    "description": "Marubun Corporation distributes electronics products in Japan and internationally. The company offers semiconductors and electronic components, including amplifiers, clocks, wired and radio interfaces, isolation products, microcomputer processors, motor drivers, power supplies, RF and microwave, sensors, ASIC/FPGA/PLDs, memories, displays, ASSP, discrete products, protective elements, passive components, connector switches, microcomputers, analog and memory ICs, wireless solutions, circuit protection, and power control components. It also provides software products, such as cloud, enterprise software, embedded software, security, and OS/development tools; measuring equipment, tester monitoring, display/DLP, and others; inspection and analysis equipment, and other products; ICT solutions, including network and storage devices, simulator tester, server, service, security, and others; and assembly and robotics comprising assembly and mounting equipment, industrial robots, service robots, and others. In addition, the company offers laser and optical parts, such as semiconductor laser, LED/light lamp, and others; embedded computer products, including CPU board, embedded system, and others; and other devices comprising IP/license, embedded module, driving simulator, and solar/photovoltaic system. Further, it provides medical devices; and development sourcing, seminars, inspection, and maintenance services. Marubun Corporation was founded in 1844 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
